{"title_page": "Alex Atala", "text_new": "{{BLP sources|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name = Alex Atala\n|image = \n|alt = \n|caption = \n|birth_name  = Milad Alexandre Mack Atala\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1968|6|3|df=yes}} \n|birth_place = [[S\u00e3o Bernardo do Campo]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]]\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|nationality = Brazilian\n|other_names = \n|known_for   = Chef of [[D.O.M. (restaurant)|D.O.M.]]\n|occupation  = Chef, restaurateur\n}}\n'''Milad Alexandre Mack Atala''' (born June 3, 1968), known as '''Alex Atala''', is a Brazilian [[chef]] of Irish and Palestinian ancestry, who runs the restaurant [[D.O.M. (restaurant)|D.O.M.]] (Latin abbreviation of ''Deo optimo maximo'') in S\u00e3o Paulo. In May 2012, D.O.M. was rated the 4th best restaurant in the world by the ''S.Pellegrino World's 50 Best Restaurants'',<ref>[http://www.theworlds50best.com/awards/1-50-winners www.theworlds50best.com top 50] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228105846/http://www.theworlds50best.com/awards/1-50-winners |date=2011-02-28 }}</ref> published by [[Restaurant magazine]]. His establishment also holds the title of \"Acqua Panna Best Restaurant In South America.\" He's known for transforming traditional Brazilian dishes, adapting French and Italian culinary techniques to native Brazilian ingredients. Atala also hosts a television show on Brazilian TV channel [[GNT]].\nIn 2013, he founded At\u00e1, an institute about relation with food, with [[Roberto Smeraldi]] and Carlos Alberto Ricardo, among others<ref>[http://www.institutoata.org.br]</ref>.\n\n== Books ==\n* ''Por uma Gastronomia Brasileira'' - Alex Atala - Editora Bei, 2003 - {{ISBN|85-86518-35-2}}\n* ''Com Unhas, Dentes & Cuca'' - Alex Atala - Editora Senac, 2008\n* ''Escoffianas Brasileiras'' - Alex Atala - Editora Larousse Brasil, 2008 - {{ISBN|978-85-7635-254-9}}\n\n== Film ==\nAlex Atala has appeared in [[Chef's Table|Chef's Table Season 2, Episode 2]].\n\n==References==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100426163916/http://www.theworlds50best.com/alex-atala-%E2%80%93-yes-we-have-priprioca-and-much-more/2908 Alex Atala \u2013 Yes we have Priprioca, and much more!] - S. Pellegrino World's 50 Best Restaurants, by Luciana Bianchi\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote|Alex Atala}}\n*[http://www.domrestaurante.com.br DOM Restaurante]\n*[http://www.dalvaedito.com.br Dalva e Dito Restaurante]\n*[http://www.institutoata.org.br/en/ At\u00e1 Institute (English version)]\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Order of Cultural Merit}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Atala, Alex}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from S\u00e3o Bernardo do Campo]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Palestinian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian DJs]]\n[[Category:Brazilian restaurateurs]]\n[[Category:Brazilian chefs]]\n[[Category:Brazilian columnists]]\n\n{{Chef-bio-stub}}\n{{Brazil-cuisine-stub}}\n{{Brazil-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{BLP sources|date=April 2008}}\n{{Infobox person\n|name = Alex Atala\n|image = \n|alt = \n|caption = \n|birth_name  = Milad Alexandre Mack Atala\n|birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1968|6|3|df=yes}} \n|birth_place = [[S\u00e3o Bernardo do Campo]], [[S\u00e3o Paulo (state)|S\u00e3o Paulo]], [[Brazil]]\n|death_date  = \n|death_place = \n|nationality = Brazilian\n|other_names = \n|known_for   = Chef of [[D.O.M. (restaurant)|D.O.M.]]\n|occupation  = Chef, restaurateur\n}}\n'''Milad Alexandre Mack Atala''' (born June 3, 1968), known as '''Alex Atala''', is a Brazilian [[chef]] of Irish and Palestinian ancestry, who runs the restaurant [[D.O.M. (restaurant)|D.O.M.]] (Latin abbreviation of ''Deo optimo maximo'') in S\u00e3o Paulo. In May 2012, D.O.M. was rated the 4th best restaurant in the world by the ''S.Pellegrino World's 50 Best Restaurants'',<ref>[http://www.theworlds50best.com/awards/1-50-winners www.theworlds50best.com top 50] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110228105846/http://www.theworlds50best.com/awards/1-50-winners |date=2011-02-28 }}</ref> published by [[Restaurant magazine]]. His establishment also holds the title of \"Acqua Panna Best Restaurant In South America.\" He's known for transforming traditional Brazilian dishes, adapting French and Italian culinary techniques to native Brazilian ingredients. Atala also hosts a television show on Brazilian TV channel [[GNT]].\nIn 2013, he founded At\u00e1, an institute about relation with food, with [[Roberto Smeraldi]] and Carlos Alberto Ricardo, among others<ref>[http://www.institutoata.org.br]</ref>\n\n== Books ==\n* ''Por uma Gastronomia Brasileira'' - Alex Atala - Editora Bei, 2003 - {{ISBN|85-86518-35-2}}\n* ''Com Unhas, Dentes & Cuca'' - Alex Atala - Editora Senac, 2008\n* ''Escoffianas Brasileiras'' - Alex Atala - Editora Larousse Brasil, 2008 - {{ISBN|978-85-7635-254-9}}\n\n== Film ==\nAlex Atala has appeared in [[Chef's Table|Chef's Table Season 2, Episode 2]].\n\n==References==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20100426163916/http://www.theworlds50best.com/alex-atala-%E2%80%93-yes-we-have-priprioca-and-much-more/2908 Alex Atala \u2013 Yes we have Priprioca, and much more!] - S. Pellegrino World's 50 Best Restaurants, by Luciana Bianchi\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote|Alex Atala}}\n*[http://www.domrestaurante.com.br DOM Restaurante]\n*[http://www.dalvaedito.com.br Dalva e Dito Restaurante]\n*[http://www.institutoata.org.br/en/ At\u00e1 Institute (English version)]\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{Order of Cultural Merit}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Atala, Alex}}\n[[Category:1968 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from S\u00e3o Bernardo do Campo]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of Palestinian descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian DJs]]\n[[Category:Brazilian restaurateurs]]\n[[Category:Brazilian chefs]]\n[[Category:Brazilian columnists]]\n\n{{Chef-bio-stub}}\n{{Brazil-cuisine-stub}}\n{{Brazil-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Nbarbettini", "label": "safe", "