:Nirvana (band) songs]]\n[[Category:Songs written by David Bowie]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Tony Visconti]]\n", "name_user": "Zmbro", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eLulu version:whoops", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Man_Who_Sold_the_World"}
{"title_page": "Shorea polyandra", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n|status = CR\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|genus = Shorea\n|species = polyandra\n|authority = P. Ashton\n}}\n\n'''''Shorea polyandra''''' (called, along with some other species in the genus ''[[Shorea]]'', '''yellow meranti''') is a [[species]] of [[plant]] in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. It is a tree [[endemism|endemic]] to [[Borneo]].\n\n==Sources==\n* {{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Shorea polyandra'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1998 | page = e.T31924A9668962 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1998 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/31924/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T31924A9668962.en | access-date = 22 December 2017}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q7501370}}\n\n[[Category:Shorea|polyandra]]\n[[Category:Endemic flora of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Trees of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Critically endangered plants]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n\n{{Dipterocarpaceae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Speciesbox\n|status = CR\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|genus = Shorea\n|species = polyandra\n|authority = P. Ashton\n}}\n\n'''''Shorea polyandra''''' (called, along with some other species in the genus ''[[Shorea]]'', '''Yellow Meranti''') is a [[species]] of [[plant]] in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. It is a tree [[endemism|endemic]] to [[Borneo]].\n\n==Sources==\n* {{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Shorea polyandra'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1998 | page = e.T31924A9668962 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1998 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/31924/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T31924A9668962.en | access-date = 22 December 2017}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q7501370}}\n\n[[Category:Shorea|polyandra]]\n[[Category:Endemic flora of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Trees of Borneo]]\n[[Category:Critically endangered plants]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n\n{{Dipterocarpaceae-stub}}\n", "name_user": "WolfmanSF", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shorea_polyandra"}
{"title_page": "Sergio Rossi (shoe designer)", "text_new": "{{short description|Italian shoe designer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{About|the person|the company named after him|Sergio Rossi}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Sergio Rossi\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|df=y|1935|7|31}}\n| birth_place   = [[San Mauro Pascoli]], Italy\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|df=y|2020|4|2|1935|7|31}}\n| death_place   = [[Cesena]], Italy\n| occupation    = Fashion designer\n| years_active  = 1951\u20132020\n| known_for     = [[Sergio Rossi]] brand\n}}\n'''Sergio Rossi''' (31 July 1935 \u2013 2 April 2020) was an Italian shoe designer, who founded [[Sergio Rossi|his own brand]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/03/italian-shoe-designer-sergio-rossi-dies-aged-84|title=Italian shoe designer, Sergio Rossi, dies aged 84|first=Ellie Violet|last=Bramley|date=3 April 2020|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[San Mauro Pascoli]], he worked with his father, a shoemaker, and learned the trade. \n\nIn 1951, he opened his first shoe store in his hometown. He also made sandals and sold them to beach-goers in [[Rimini]] and at [[Bologna]] boutiques. In 1968, the first shoes, marked with the Rossi brand, were produced.\n\nIn March 2020, Rossi and his company donated [[Euro sign|\u20ac]]100,000 to the [[Ospedale Luigi Sacco]] in [[Milan]], in a joint effort from the fashion industry to combat the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|coronavirus pandemic in Italy]].<ref>[https://www.businessoffashion.com/articles/intelligence/in-the-face-of-a-global-crisis-what-is-the-fashion-industry-doing In the Face of a Global Crisis, What Is the Fashion Industry Doing?]</ref> On 2 April 2020, Rossi died in [[Cesena]] from [[coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] at the age of 84.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/accessories-news/footwear/footwear-legend-sergio-rossi-dies-84-coronavirus-1203553603/|title=Sergio Rossi Dies at 84|first1=Katie|last1=Abel|first2=Luisa|last2=Zargani|date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nRossi's son Gianvito is also a shoe designer with his own eponymous brand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/community/people/gianvito-rossi|title=Gianvito Rossi|date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rossi, Sergio}}\n[[Category:1935 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Shoemakers]]\n[[Category:Italian fashion designers]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Forl\u00ec-Cesena]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy]]\n[[Category:Italian business executives]]\n[[Category:Italian company founders]]\n\n{{Italy-artist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Italian shoe designer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{About|the person|the company named after him|Sergio Rossi}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Sergio Rossi\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date|df=y|1935|7|31}}\n| birth_place   = [[San Mauro Pascoli]], Italy\n| death_date    = {{Death date and age|df=y|2020|4|3|1935|7|31}}\n| death_place   = [[Cesena]], Italy\n| occupation    = Fashion designer\n| years_active  = 1951\u20132020\n| known_for     = [[Sergio Rossi]] brand\n}}\n'''Sergio Rossi''' (31 July 1935 \u2013 3 April 2020) was an Italian shoe designer, who founded [[Sergio Rossi|his own brand]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2020/apr/03/italian-shoe-designer-sergio-rossi-dies-aged-84|title=Italian shoe designer, Sergio Rossi, dies aged 84|first=Ellie Violet|last=Bramley|date=3 April 2020|via=www.theguardian.com}}</ref>\n\n==Biography==\nBorn in [[San Mauro Pascoli]], he worked with his father, a shoemaker, and learned the trade. \n\nIn 1951, he opened his first shoe store in his hometown. He also made sandals and sold them to beach-goers in [[Rimini]] and at [[Bologna]] boutiques. In 1968, the first shoes, marked with the Rossi brand, were produced.\n\nIn March 2020, Rossi and his company donated [[Euro sign|\u20ac]]100,000 to the [[Ospedale Luigi Sacco]] in [[Milan]], in a joint effort from the fashion industry to combat the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy|coronavirus pandemic in Italy]].<ref>[https://www.businessoffashion.com/articles/intelligence/in-the-face-of-a-global-crisis-what-is-the-fashion-industry-doing In the Face of a Global Crisis, What Is the Fashion Industry Doing?]</ref> On 3 April 2020, Rossi died in [[Cesena]] from [[coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] at the age of 84.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://wwd.com/accessories-news/footwear/footwear-legend-sergio-rossi-dies-84-coronavirus-1203553603/|title=Sergio Rossi Dies at 84|first1=Katie|last1=Abel|first2=Luisa|last2=Zargani|date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nRossi's son Gianvito is also a shoe designer with his own eponymous brand.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/community/people/gianvito-rossi|title=Gianvito Rossi|date=3 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Rossi, Sergio}}\n[[Category:1935 births]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:Shoemakers]]\n[[Category:Italian fashion designers]]\n[[Category:People from the Province of Forl\u00ec-Cesena]]\n[[Category:Deaths from the 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Italy]]\n[[Category:Italian business executives]]\n[[Category:Italian company founders]]\n\n{{Italy-artist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "CAWylie", "label": "safe", "comment": "Died 2 April", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sergio_Rossi_(shoe_designer)"}
