{"title_page": "Shorea maxima", "text_new": "{{Taxobox\n|image=Shorea maxima - branche basse.JPG \n|status = EN\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|regnum = [[Plantae]]\n|unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]]\n|unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]]\n|unranked_ordo = [[Rosids]]\n|ordo = [[Malvales]]\n|familia = [[Dipterocarpaceae]]\n|genus = ''[[Shorea]]''\n|species = '''''S. maxima'''''\n|binomial = ''Shorea maxima''\n|binomial_authority = (King) Sym.\n|}}\n\n'''''Shorea maxima''''' (also called '''yellow meranti''') is a species of [[plant]] in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. It is a tree [[endemism|endemic]] to [[Peninsular Malaysia]].\n\n==References==\n* {{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Shorea maxima'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] | volume = 1998 | page = e.T31436A9634594 | publisher = [[IUCN]] | date = 1998 | url = http://www.iucnredlist.org/details/31436/0 | doi = 10.2305/IUCN.UK.1998.RLTS.T31436A9634594.en | access-date = 22 December 2017}}\n\n{{Taxonbar|from=Q3482505}}\n\n[[Category:Shorea|maxima]]\n[[Category:Endemic flora of Peninsular Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Trees of Peninsular Malaysia]]\n[[Category:Endangered plants]]\n[[Category:Taxonomy articles created by Polbot]]\n\n\n{{Dipterocarpaceae-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Taxobox\n|image=Shorea maxima - branche basse.JPG \n|status = EN\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|regnum = [[Plantae]]\n|unranked_divisio = [[Angiosperms]]\n|unranked_classis = [[Eudicots]]\n|unranked_ordo = [[Rosids]]\n|ordo = [[Malvales]]\n|familia = [[Dipterocarpaceae]]\n|genus = ''[[Shorea]]''\n|species = '''''S. maxima'''''\n|binomial = ''Shorea maxima''\n|binomial_authority = (King) Sym.\n|}}\n\n'''''Shorea maxima''''' (also called '''Yellow Meranti''') is a species of [[plant]] in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. It is a tree [[endemism|endemic]] to [[Peninsular Malaysia]].\n\n==References==\n* {{Cite journal | author = Ashton, P. | title = ''Shorea maxima'' | journal = [[The IUCN Red List of Threatened Species]] 