{"title_page": "A\u015fub Sultan", "text_new": "{{Infobox royalty\n| consort      = yes\n| name         = A\u015fub Sultan \n| image        = Suleymaniye Mausoleum Suleyman mausoleum 1230.jpg\n| caption      = <small>The resting place of ''Saliha Dil-A\u015fub Valide Sultan'' is located at the [[mausoleum]] of [[Suleyman the Magnificent]] inside the [[S\u00fcleymaniye Mosque]] in [[Fatih]].</small>\n|succession    = [[Valide sultan|Valide Sultan]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]]\n| reign        = 8 November 1687&nbsp;\u2013 3 January 1690\n| predecessor  = [[Turhan Sultan]]\n| successor    = [[G\u00fclnu\u015f Sultan]]\n| succession2  = [[Haseki Sultan]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]]<br />{{small|(Imperial Consort)}}\n| reign2       = 1642 \u2013 12 August 1648\n| regent2      = [[Turhan Sultan|Turhan]]<br />[[Muazzez Sultan|Muazzez]]<br />[[H\u00fcma\u015fah Sultan (wife of Ibrahim)|H\u00fcma\u015fah]]<br />Ay\u015fe<br />Mah\u0131enver<br />[[\u015eivekar Sultan|\u0218ivekar]]<br />Sa\u00e7ba\u011fl\u0131\n| reg-type2    = Co-Haseki\n| spouse       = [[Ibrahim of the Ottoman Empire|Ibrahim]]\n| issue        = [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]]\n| full name    = {{lang-tr|A\u015fub Sultan}}<br>{{lang-ota|\u0627\u0634\u0648\u0628 \u0633\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0646}}\n| house        = [[Ottoman dynasty|Ottoman]] (by marriage)\n| father       = \n| mother       =\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = \n| birth_place  = \n| death_date   = 3 January 1690\n| death_place  = [[Edirne Palace]], [[Edirne]], [[Ottoman Empire]]\n| burial_place = [[S\u00fcleymaniye Mosque]], [[Istanbul]]\n| religion     = [[Sunni Islam]]\n}}\n[[File:Rijeka033.jpg|thumb|262px|The son of ''Saliha Dil-A\u015fub [[Valide Sultan]],'' [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]]]]\n'''A\u015fub Sultan'''{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=96}}{{Cref2|a}} ({{lang-ota|\u0627\u0634\u0648\u0628 \u0633\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0646}}; died 3 January 1690) was a consort of Ottoman Sultan [[Ibrahim of the Ottoman Empire|Ibrahim]] and [[Valide Sultan]] to their son [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Peirce |first=Leslie |authorlink=Leslie Peirce |title=The Imperial Harem: Women and Sovereignty in the Ottoman Empire|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|year=1993|isbn=0-19-508677-5|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=L6-VRgVzRcUC|page=108}}</ref>\n\n==Life==\nA\u015fub was born in 1627 in [[Serbia]] her birth name was Katarina. She became the consort of Ibrahim and on 15 April 1642, gave birth to her only son, \u015eehzade Suleiman (future [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]]). During Ibrahim's reign her stipend consisted of 1,300 aspers a day.<ref>{{cite book|first=Lucienne|last=Thys-\u015eenocak|title=Ottoman Women Builders: The Architectural Patronage of Hadice Turhan Sultan|publisher=Ashgate|year=2006|pages=89|isbn=978-0-754-63310-5}}</ref> He also gifted the incomes of [[Bolu Sanjak]] to her.<ref>{{cite book|first=|last=|title=Resimli tarih mecmuasi|publisher=Iskit Yayinevi|year=1956|pages=229|isbn=}}</ref> She was described as a simple-hearted woman of unruly character.{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=96}} She was deeply loved by Ibrahim, and was his favorite consort although she was not his legal wife.\n\nAfter the deposition and death of Sultan Ibrahim in 1648, his eldest son, [[Mehmed IV]] ascended the throne, after which A\u015fub settled in the Old Palace. This brought her thirty-nine years of imprisonment in the Old Palace.{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=97}}\n\nShe was hoping that the conflict between Mehmed's mother, [[Turhan Hatice Sultan|Turhan Sultan]], her mother-in-law, [[K\u00f6sem Sultan]] would change her fortune in that she would become the Valide Sultan herself. K\u00f6sem was planning to kill her daughter-in-law and dethrone her grandson Sultan Mehmed with the help of some high officers in the yeni\u00e7eri corps, and to place \u015eehzade Suleiman, on the throne. However, [[Meleki Hatun]] warned Turhan who managed to strangle her mother-in-law with the help of the eunuchs in the Harem in 1651. A\u015fub herself was spared from execution since she was suspected in plotting against Turhan and her son, the Sultan. <ref>{{cite book|first=Esin|last=Akalin|title=Staging the Ottoman Turk: British Drama, 1656\u00d01792|publisher=Columbia University Press|date=October 11, 2016|pages=225|isbn=978-3-838-26919-1}}</ref>{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=96-7}} \n\nIn 1672-73, she created an endowment at Istanbul.<ref>{{cite book|author=Narodna biblioteka \"Sv. sv. Kiril i Metodi\u012d. Orientalski otdel, International Centre for Minority Studies and Intercultural Relations, Research Centre for Islamic History, Art, and Culture|title=Inventory of Ottoman Turkish documents about Waqf preserved in the Oriental Department at the St. St. Cyril and Methodius National Library: Registers|publisher=Narodna biblioteka \"Sv. sv. Kiril i Metodi\u012d|year=2003|pages=116, 214|isbn=}}</ref>\n\nIn 1687 Mehmed IV was deposed and the throne was overtaken by Suleiman II, the son of A\u015fub and she became the next [[Valide sultan]].{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=349-50}} In July 1688, she followed her son to Edirne.{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=350}}\n\n==Death==\nShe died in the [[Edirne Palace]] on 3 January 1690, having been ill and bedridden for an year. She was buried in the mausoleum of [[Suleiman the Magnificent]] in [[S\u00fcleymaniye Mosque]], [[Istanbul]].{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=350}}{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=97}}\n\n==In popular culture==\nIn the 2010 Turkish historical film ''Mahpeyker: K\u00f6sem Sultan'', A\u015fub Sultan is portrayed by Turkish actress G\u00f6kcan G\u00f6kmen.<ref>{{Citation|title=Mahpeyker - K\u00f6sem Sultan (2010)|url=https://m.imdb.com/title/tt1754166/|accessdate=2019-10-07}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2015 [[Turkey|Turkish]] historical non-fiction TV series [[Muhte\u015fem Y\u00fczy\u0131l: K\u00f6sem]], A\u015fub Sultan is portrayed by Turkish actress Ece G\u00fczel.<ref>{{Citation|title=Muhtesem Y\u00fczyil: K\u00f6sem (TV Series 2015\u20132017) Poster Muhtesem Y\u00fczyil: K\u00f6sem (2015\u20132017)|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4787028/characters/nm9618373|accessdate=2019-10-07}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ottoman family tree]]\n*[[List of the mothers of the Ottoman Sultans]]\n*[[List of consorts of the Ottoman Sultans]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Cnote2 Begin|liststyle=upper-alpha}}\n{{Cnote2|a|She is either called A\u015fub Sultan, A\u015fube, or Saliha Dila\u015fub.{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=349}}}}\n{{Cnote2 End}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book|first=M. \u00c7a\u011fatay|last=Ulu\u00e7ay|title=Padi\u015fahlar\u0131n kad\u0131nlar\u0131 ve k\u0131zlar\u0131|year=2011|publisher=\u00d6t\u00fcken|isbn=978-9-754-37840-5}}\n*{{cite book|first=Necdet|last=Sakao\u011flu|title=Bu M\u00fclk\u00fcn Kad\u0131n Sultanlar\u0131: V\u00e2lide Sultanlar, H\u00e2tunlar, Hasekiler, Kand\u0131nefendiler, Sultanefendiler|publisher=O\u011flak Yay\u0131nc\u0131l\u0131k|year=2008|isbn=978-6-051-71079-2}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-roy|tr}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ay\u015fe Sultan (wife of Murad IV)|Ay\u015fe Sultan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Haseki Sultan]]|years=until 12 August 1648<br />''concurrently with [[Turhan Sultan|Turhan]], [[H\u00fcma\u015fah Sultan (wife of Ibrahim)|H\u00fcma\u015fah]], [[Muazzez Sultan|Muazzez]], Ay\u015fe, Mahenver, [[\u015eivekar Sultan|\u0218ivekar]], and Sa\u00e7ba\u011fl\u0131''}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[G\u00fclnu\u015f Sultan]]}}\n{{succession box|title=[[List of Valide Sultans|Valide Sultan]]|before=[[Turhan Hatice Sultan|Turhan Sultan]]|after=[[G\u00fclnu\u015f Sultan]]|years=8 November 1687&nbsp;\u2013 4 December 1689}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Ottoman Dynasty}}\n{{Mothers of the Ottoman Sultans}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Asub Sultan}}\n[[Category:Year of birth unknown]]\n[[Category:1689 deaths]]\n[[Category:Wives of Ottoman Sultans]]\n[[Category:17th-century Ottoman royalty]]\n[[Category:Valide sultan]]\n[[Category:Concubines of the Ottoman Empire]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox royalty\n| consort      = yes\n| name         = A\u015fub Sultan \n| image        = Suleymaniye Mausoleum Suleyman mausoleum 1230.jpg\n| caption      = <small>The resting place of ''Saliha Dil-A\u015fub Valide Sultan'' is located at the [[mausoleum]] of [[Suleyman the Magnificent]] inside the [[S\u00fcleymaniye Mosque]] in [[Fatih]].</small>\n|succession    = [[Valide sultan|Valide Sultan]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]]\n| reign        = 8 November 1687&nbsp;\u2013 3 January 1690\n| predecessor  = [[Turhan Sultan]]\n| successor    = [[G\u00fclnu\u015f Sultan]]\n| succession2  = [[Haseki Sultan]] of the [[Ottoman Empire]]<br />{{small|(Imperial Consort)}}\n| reign2       = 1642 \u2013 12 August 1648\n| regent2      = [[Turhan Sultan|Turhan]]<br />[[Muazzez Sultan|Muazzez]]<br />[[H\u00fcma\u015fah Sultan (wife of Ibrahim)|H\u00fcma\u015fah]]<br />Ay\u015fe<br />Mah\u0131enver<br />[[\u015eivekar Sultan|\u0218ivekar]]<br />Sa\u00e7ba\u011fl\u0131\n| reg-type2    = Co-Haseki\n| spouse       = [[Ibrahim of the Ottoman Empire|Ibrahim]]\n| issue        = [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]]\n| full name    = {{lang-tr|A\u015fub Sultan}}<br>{{lang-ota|\u0627\u0634\u0648\u0628 \u0633\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0646}}\n| house        = [[Ottoman dynasty|Ottoman]] (by marriage)\n| father       = \n| mother       =\n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = \n| birth_place  = \n| death_date   = 3 January 1690\n| death_place  = [[Edirne Palace]], [[Edirne]], [[Ottoman Empire]]\n| burial_place = [[S\u00fcleymaniye Mosque]], [[Istanbul]]\n| religion     = [[Sunni Islam]]\n}}\n[[File:Rijeka033.jpg|thumb|262px|The son of ''Saliha Dil-A\u015fub [[Valide Sultan]],'' [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]]]]\n'''A\u015fub Sultan'''{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=96}}{{Cref2|a}} ({{lang-ota|\u0627\u0634\u0648\u0628 \u0633\u0644\u0637\u0627\u0646}}; died 3 January 1690) was a consort of Ottoman Sultan [[Ibrahim of the Ottoman Empire|Ibrahim]] and [[Valide Sultan]] to their son [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]].<ref>{{cite book |last=Peirce |first=Leslie |authorlink=Leslie Peirce |title=The Imperial Harem: Women and Sovereignty in the Ottoman Empire|publisher=[[Oxford University Press]]|year=1993|isbn=0-19-508677-5|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=L6-VRgVzRcUC|page=108}}</ref>\n\n==Life==\nA\u015fub was born in 1627 in [[Serbia]] her birth name was Katarina. She became the consort of Ibrahim and on 15 April 1642, gave birth to her only son, \u015eehzade Suleiman (future [[Suleiman II of the Ottoman Empire|Suleiman II]]). During Ibrahim's reign her stipend consisted of 1,300 aspers a day.<ref>{{cite book|first=Lucienne|last=Thys-\u015eenocak|title=Ottoman Women Builders: The Architectural Patronage of Hadice Turhan Sultan|publisher=Ashgate|year=2006|pages=89|isbn=978-0-754-63310-5}}</ref> He also gifted the incomes of [[Bolu Sanjak]] to her.<ref>{{cite book|first=|last=|title=Resimli tarih mecmuasi|publisher=Iskit Yayinevi|year=1956|pages=229|isbn=}}</ref> She was described as a simple hearted woman of unruly character.{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=96}} She was deeply loved by Ibrahim , and was his favorite consort although she was not his legal wife.\n\nAfter the deposition and death of Sultan Ibrahim in 1648, his eldest son, [[Mehmed IV]] ascended the throne, after which A\u015fub settled in the Old Palace. This brought her thirty nine years of imprisonment in the Old Palace.{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=97}}\n\nShe was hoping that the conflict between Mehmed's mother, [[Turhan Hatice Sultan|Turhan Sultan]], her mother-in-law, [[K\u00f6sem Sultan]] would change her fortune in that she would became the Valide Sultan herself. K\u00f6sem was planning to kill her daughter-in-law and dethrone her grandson Sultan Mehmed with the help of some high officers in the yeni\u00e7eri corps, and to place \u015eehzade Suleiman, on the throne. However, [[Meleki Hatun]] warned Turhan who managed to strangle her mother-in-law with the help of the eunuchs in the Harem in 1651. A\u015fub herself was spared from execution since she was suspected in plotting against Turhan and her son , the Sultan. <ref>{{cite book|first=Esin|last=Akalin|title=Staging the Ottoman Turk: British Drama, 1656\u00d01792|publisher=Columbia University Press|date=October 11, 2016|pages=225|isbn=978-3-838-26919-1}}</ref>{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=96-7}} \n\nIn 1672-73, she created an endowment at Istanbul.<ref>{{cite book|author=Narodna biblioteka \"Sv. sv. Kiril i Metodi\u012d. Orientalski otdel, International Centre for Minority Studies and Intercultural Relations, Research Centre for Islamic History, Art, and Culture|title=Inventory of Ottoman Turkish documents about Waqf preserved in the Oriental Department at the St. St. Cyril and Methodius National Library: Registers|publisher=Narodna biblioteka \"Sv. sv. Kiril i Metodi\u012d|year=2003|pages=116, 214|isbn=}}</ref>\n\nIn 1687 Mehmed IV was deposed and the throne was overtaken by Suleiman II, the son of A\u015fub and she became the next [[Valide sultan]].{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=349-50}} In July 1688, she followed her son to Edirne.{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=350}}\n\n==Death==\nShe died in the [[Edirne Palace]] on 3 January 1690, having been ill and bedridden for an year. She was buried in the mausoleum of [[Suleiman the Magnificent]] in [[S\u00fcleymaniye Mosque]], [[Istanbul]].{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=350}}{{sfn|Ulu\u00e7ay|2011|p=97}}\n\n==In popular culture==\nIn the 2010 Turkish historical film ''Mahpeyker: K\u00f6sem Sultan'', A\u015fub Sultan is portrayed by Turkish acress G\u00f6kcan G\u00f6kmen.<ref>{{Citation|title=Mahpeyker - K\u00f6sem Sultan (2010)|url=https://m.imdb.com/title/tt1754166/|accessdate=2019-10-07}}</ref>\n\nIn the 2015 [[Turkey|Turkish]] historical non-fiction TV series [[Muhte\u015fem Y\u00fczy\u0131l: K\u00f6sem]], A\u015fub Sultan is portrayed by Turkish actress Ece G\u00fczel.<ref>{{Citation|title=Muhtesem Y\u00fczyil: K\u00f6sem (TV Series 2015\u20132017) Poster Muhtesem Y\u00fczyil: K\u00f6sem (2015\u20132017)|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt4787028/characters/nm9618373|accessdate=2019-10-07}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Ottoman family tree]]\n*[[List of the mothers of the Ottoman Sultans]]\n*[[List of consorts of the Ottoman Sultans]]\n\n==Notes==\n{{Cnote2 Begin|liststyle=upper-alpha}}\n{{Cnote2|a|She is either called A\u015fub Sultan, A\u015fube, or Saliha Dila\u015fub.{{sfn|Sakao\u011flu|2008|p=349}}}}\n{{Cnote2 End}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==Sources==\n*{{cite book|first=M. \u00c7a\u011fatay|last=Ulu\u00e7ay|title=Padi\u015fahlar\u0131n kad\u0131nlar\u0131 ve k\u0131zlar\u0131|year=2011|publisher=\u00d6t\u00fcken|isbn=978-9-754-37840-5}}\n*{{cite book|first=Necdet|last=Sakao\u011flu|title=Bu M\u00fclk\u00fcn Kad\u0131n Sultanlar\u0131: V\u00e2lide Sultanlar, H\u00e2tunlar, Hasekiler, Kand\u0131nefendiler, Sultanefendiler|publisher=O\u011flak Yay\u0131nc\u0131l\u0131k|year=2008|isbn=978-6-051-71079-2}}\n\n{{s-start}}\n{{s-roy|tr}}\n{{s-bef|before=[[Ay\u015fe Sultan (wife of Murad IV)|Ay\u015fe Sultan]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[Haseki Sultan]]|years=until 12 August 1648<br />''concurrently with [[Turhan Sultan|Turhan]], [[H\u00fcma\u015fah Sultan (wife of Ibrahim)|H\u00fcma\u015fah]], [[Muazzez Sultan|Muazzez]], Ay\u015fe, Mahenver, [[\u015eivekar Sultan|\u0218ivekar]], and Sa\u00e7ba\u011fl\u0131''}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[G\u00fclnu\u015f Sultan]]}}\n{{succession box|title=[[List of Valide Sultans|Valide Sultan]]|before=[[Turhan Hatice Sultan|Turhan Sultan]]|after=[[G\u00fclnu\u015f Sultan]]|years=8 November 1687&nbsp;\u2013 4 December 1689}}\n{{s-end}}\n\n{{Ottoman Dynasty}}\n{{Mothers of the Ottoman Sultans}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Asub Sultan}}\n[[Category:Year of birth unknown]]\n[[Category:1689 deaths]]\n[[Category:Wives of Ottoman Sultans]]\n[[Category:17th-century Ottoman royalty]]\n[[Category:Valide sultan]]\n[[Category:Concubines of the Ottoman Empire]]\n", "name_user": "LilHelpa", "label": 