{"title_page": "Shorea gibbosa", "text_new": "{{Speciesbox\n|status = CR\n|status_system = IUCN2.3\n|status_ref = <ref name=IUCN/>\n|genus = Shorea\n|species = gibbosa\n|authority = [[Dietrich Brandis|Brandis]]<ref name=Ashton/>\n}}\n\n'''''Shorea gibbosa''''' (also called '''yellow meranti''') is a large [[Tropical rainforest#Emergent layer|emergent]] [[rainforest]] [[tree]] [[species]] in the family [[Dipterocarpaceae]]. It is native to [[Sumatra]], [[Borneo]], [[Peninsular Malaysia]] and [[Singapore]].<ref name=Ashton/> The tallest measured specimen is 81.1 metres tall, in the [[Tawau Hills National Park]], in [[Sabah]] on the island of [[Borneo]].<ref name=Borneo/>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist | 30em | refs =\n\n<ref name=IUCN>Ashton, P. 1998. [https://www.iucnredlist.org/details/33700/all ''Shorea gibbosa'']. [http://www.iucnredlist.org 2006 IUCN Red List of Threatened Species.] Downloaded on 23 August 2007.</ref>\n\n<ref name=Ashton>{{Cite book | last1 = Ashton | first1 = P. S. | date = September 2004 | contribution = ''Shorea gibbosa'' Brandis | contribution-url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/backup/TFSS.vol4_5_6.pdf | editor1-last = Soepadmo | editor1-first = E. | editor2-last = Saw | editor2-first = L. G. | editor3-last = Chung | editor3-first = R. C. K. | title = Tree Flora of Sabah and Sarawak | volume = 5 | pages = 262\u2013263 | publisher = [[Forest Research Institute Malaysia]] | isbn = 983-2181-59-3 | url = http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | version = (free online from the publisher, lesser resolution scan PDF versions) | accessdate = 18 April 2008 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20130927074942/http://www.chm.frim.gov.my/Resources/Publications/Books/Floras/Tree-Flora-of-Sabah-and-Sarawak.aspx | archive-date = 27 September 2013 | url-status = dead }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=Borneo>{{cite web | url = http://www.nativetreesociety.org/worldtrees/sea_ei/borneo_ii.htm | title = Borneo |